{"id":14880744,"mediaExerciseId":"81a4bd65-9de3-4544-8568-bbed3057293d","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"2","chapterTitle":"Financial Statements, Taxes, and Cash Flow","groupId":612264,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":42,"solutions":[{"id":5977157,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"For this exercise, we will explain whether it is possible to have negative equity under market values the same way happening when liabilities exceed assets measured at cost.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/b598c26debc5d27845910fff09ea9a63/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/b598c26debc5d27845910fff09ea9a63/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Market value** is the amount at which an entity can sell its asset in the market. Factors affecting items' market values include supply and demand, industry, company performance, economic status, and the like. Market values are primarily assessed to determine current prices and reduce confusion about the actual worth of an item.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":176,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/0086d4990a8120a8c17670b61e60c1ae/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/0086d4990a8120a8c17670b61e60c1ae/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Concerning accounting standards, it is **possible** that an entity's liabilities would exceed its assets under **insolvency**. A business is insolvent when its total resources are insufficient to satisfy all creditors' claims, making **equity balance negative**. Under this condition, business owners would expect to receive nothing as all assets are not enough to pay off all entity's debts.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":212,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/c121d0a2981e9c285cc614e3ce082378/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":107,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/c121d0a2981e9c285cc614e3ce082378/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Similarly, a negative equity balance **can still exist** even if assets and liabilities were measured at market values. There is no such limitation imposed on measuring an entity's resources and obligations concerning market prices.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/7b8236adf71e346d1719e4b032704c04/lateximg_large.png","width":1011},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/7b8236adf71e346d1719e4b032704c04/lateximg.png","width":505}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"However, bankruptcy laws mandated that entities must not have negative equity. Meaning, although possible, it is not allowed that liabilities would exceed assets - otherwise, an individual or business must liquidate or file bankruptcy.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/959e5a2e7c7e6294e4e83c980a1607ed/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/b1860ea320fd367dc2adc91bac09113a/959e5a2e7c7e6294e4e83c980a1607ed/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"288ece77-36df-47ed-9bbb-28a7ae5048c5","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5},{"id":5899657,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to explain if market values can be negative.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/17/fa549dedb5b9bde196f6b96a2389f249/4005b80cc87115e4db8759b6932e6082/lateximg_large.png","width":909},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/17/fa549dedb5b9bde196f6b96a2389f249/4005b80cc87115e4db8759b6932e6082/lateximg.png","width":455}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**It is impossible to have a negative market value**. This indicates that no investor, regardless of price, is willing to purchase the stock. In both corporate and individual bankruptcy law, a company's equity cannot be negative, which means that liabilities cannot exceed assets in market value.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/17/fa549dedb5b9bde196f6b96a2389f249/1320bf00cd2b7ec31f826cb6fefde6e5/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/17/fa549dedb5b9bde196f6b96a2389f249/1320bf00cd2b7ec31f826cb6fefde6e5/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"See the explanation\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/17/fa549dedb5b9bde196f6b96a2389f249/2e76b159fcb3366430a475ac06032f7e/lateximg_large.png","width":259},"regular":{"height":14,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/17/fa549dedb5b9bde196f6b96a2389f249/2e76b159fcb3366430a475ac06032f7e/lateximg.png","width":131}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"87b89b04-dfd4-469a-ada4-4714658e4055","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880745,"exerciseName":"6","page":42,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"42f8f4fd-ab7d-46ca-8331-803c59b17f4c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-critical-thinking-questions-6-42f8f4fd-ab7d-46ca-8331-803c59b17f4c"},{"id":14880746,"exerciseName":"7","page":42,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7ead2354-2ca0-4d31-a53d-4d50284a3fb2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-critical-thinking-questions-7-7ead2354-2ca0-4d31-a53d-4d50284a3fb2"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880743,"exerciseName":"4","page":42,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a2a2189f-6fee-4411-8f79-b9a0e5dd5c93","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-critical-thinking-questions-4-a2a2189f-6fee-4411-8f79-b9a0e5dd5c93"},{"id":14880742,"exerciseName":"3","page":42,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ab818ea2-a7ac-4340-a63a-6a4cf8a95912","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-critical-thinking-questions-3-ab818ea2-a7ac-4340-a63a-6a4cf8a95912"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-critical-thinking-questions-5-81a4bd65-9de3-4544-8568-bbed3057293d"}